            <html:p>Notice, though, that we can ignore the row and the column headed by "<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {\mathbf {B}}]]></fr:tex>".
After all, we're supposing that both <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> have the property, and that means that both  <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u(A)]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u(B)]]></fr:tex> must not be <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {\mathbf {B}}]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
            <html:p>Look at it, then, more like this:</html:p>
            <html:table style="border-collapse: collapse;">
  <html:thead><html:tr>
    <html:td class="topedge leftedge"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lor ]]></fr:tex></html:td>
